üìù Brief Description about Blogify (full-stack blogging platform)

Blogify is a full-stack blogging platform where users can create, edit, and share blogs while interacting through comments 
in a secure, authenticated environment. The platform integrates modern UI/UX, role-based access control, structured validation,
and database modeling to deliver a smooth and responsive user experience. 
With its clean architecture and neon-themed design, the project demonstrates practical knowledge of backend systems, 
authentication workflows, CRUD operations, and modern frontend styling.

‚≠ê Project Highlights 

1. Implemented complete Blog CRUD functionality:
   Users can create, edit, delete, and view detailed blog posts.

2. Developed secure user authentication:
   Handled using Passport.js and session management for safe login/logout.

3. Built personalized user profiles:
   Every user has a dedicated profile showing all their published blogs.

4. Integrated an interactive comments system:
   Users can comment on blogs, delete their own comments, and blog owners can moderate.

5. Designed a modern neon-glass UI:
   Custom CSS with gradients, glassmorphism, and metallic navy-blue forms.

6. Ensured data validation & input safety:
   Used Joi validation and ObjectId checks to prevent malformed or malicious inputs.

7. Protected routes with authorization checks:
   Only the author of a blog/comment can modify or delete it.

8. Followed a structured MVC-inspired architecture:
   Clean separation of routes, models, middleware, and views.

9. Implemented flash message feedback:
   Users receive instant visual responses for actions such as login, logout, or errors.

10. Created responsive, mobile-friendly layouts:
    Works smoothly across mobile, tablet, and desktop.